expr

Class Expr

  • java.lang.Object
    • expr.Expr
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BinaryExpr, Num, Variable

    public abstract class Expr
extends Object
    An Expr object represents a real valued expression that may contain variables. The value of a variable is obtained from an Environment object by specifying the name of the variable.
    Author:
    Lennart Andersson
    See Also:
    Environment
